@database "HTTPR_Rexx_english.guide"
@author Andrija Antonijevic
@remark $VER: HTTPR_Rexx_english.guide 1.8 (8.12.99)
@smartwrap

@node MAIN "Arexx commands"

@{line}Here is list and short explanations of HTTPResume's ARexx
comands:@{par}
@{lindent 2}

@{"     ABORT     " link Abort}@{line}
@{"    ICONIFY    " link Iconify}@{line}
@{" JUMPTOSCREEN  " link JumpToScreen}@{line}
@{"     QUERY...  " link Query}@{line}
@{"      QUIT     " link Quit}@{line}
@{" SCREENTOFRONT " link ScreenToFront}@{line}
@{"      SET...   " link Set}@{line}
@{"     START     " link Start}@{line}
@{"   UNICONIFY   " link Uniconify}@{line}
@{"  UNZIPWINDOW  " link UnzipWindow}@{line}
@{"   ZIPWINDOW   " link ZipWindow}@{line}
@{lindent 0}

@endnode
@node START "START"

@{line}@{b}START@{ub}@{par}

Starts downloading a file. Please also read @{" this " link Important}.

@endnode
@node ABORT "ABORT"

@{line}@{b}ABORT@{ub}@{par}

Aborts current download. Please also read @{" this " link Important}.

@endnode
@node ICONIFY "ICONIFY"

@{line}@{b}ICONIFY@{ub}@{par}

Iconifies HTTPResume window if it's not already iconified. Please also
read @{" this " link Important}.

@endnode
@node UNICONIFY "UNICONIFY"

@{line}@{b}UNICONIFY@{ub}@{par}

Uniconifies HTTPResume window if it's not already uniconified. Please
also read @{" this " link Important}.

@endnode
@node QUIT "QUIT"

@{line}@{b}QUIT@{ub}@{par}

Quits HTTPResume regardless of QUICKQUIT. Please also read
@{" this " link Important}.

@endnode
@node IMPORTANT "Important"

@{line}When you send one of these commands to HTTPResume, they will just
signal HTTPResume what to do and return immediately!@{par}

This means that if you send @{b}START@{ub} and want to know when
HTTPResume finished downloading you will have to loop-wait and
@{" QUERY FINISHED " link Query} (see later) to find out what happened.

@endnode
@node SCREENTOFRONT "SCREENTOFRONT"

@{line}@{b}SCREENTOFRONT@{ub}@{par}

Brings screen on which @{b}HTTPResume's window@{ub} is on to front. Sets
RC to 5 if there's no screen (f. ex. if it's iconified).

@endnode
@node ZIPWINDOW "ZIPWINDOW"

@{line}@{b}ZIPWINDOW@{ub}@{par}

Changes HTTPResume window (if open) to small size. If HTTPResume
is iconified, it tells it to start zipped when GUI opens again.

@endnode
@node UNZIPWINDOW "UNZIPWINDOW"

@{line}@{b}UNZIPWINDOW@{ub}@{par}

Changes HTTPResume window (if open) to normal size. If HTTPResume
is iconified and it's supposed to start zipped, after you issue this
command it won't do it.

@endnode
@node JUMPTOSCREEN "JUMPTOSCREEN"

@{line}@{b}JUMPTOSCREEN@{ub} <public screen name>@{par}

Jumps to specified public screen name. If there's no screen with
that name, HTTPResume will reopen its GUI on default public screen.

@endnode
@node QUERY "QUERY"

@{line}@{b}QUERY@{ub}@{par}

Possible values to be querried are:@{par}

@{b}STATUS, FINISHED, URL, OUTFILE, PROXY, RANGE, OVERWRITE, NOCACHE,
GMTOFFSET, NODATECHECK, AUTORESUME, ATTEMPTS, DELAY, PUBSCREEN,
STARTDIR, TREE, CONVFROM, CONVTO, MAXNAMELEN, REFERER, WINX, WINY,
WINWIDTH, WINHEIGHT, FONTNAME, FONTSIZE, USESYSFONT, NOPROXY,
QUICKQUIT, OKSOUND, ERRSOUND, NOWINACTIVATE, CREATEICONS,
AREXXCONSOLE, ONLYIFUPDATED, KEEPDATE, TIMEOUT, MAXTIMEOUTS,
MINCPS, IGNORECPS, NOERRREQ, VERSION, FORCECOMMENT, WINDOWTITLE,
USERAGENT@{ub}@{par}

@{b}STATUS@{ub} returns number of bytes read so far, number of bytes
that should be read during current download (0 if unknown), size of
file on local disk before the download started, seconds that passed so
far and if server supports resuming (+-?). For example, if you get
"3862 12426 806497 2 +" it means that file on server is 818923
(806497+12426) bytes long and that there were 806497 bytes on local
disk before resume was attempted leaving HTTPResume to read 12426
bytes. 3862 bytes of that 12426 bytes are read in two seconds so far
and the server supports resuming. Seconds get updated along with other
data, not every second. If HTTPResume is not downloading, you will
receive "-1 -1 -1 -1 ?".@{par}

@{b}FINISHED@{ub} returns 1 if HTTPResume is still downloading file, 0
if it has finished downloading and there were no errors and negative
number if there were errors during download.@{par}

@{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub} returns name of the public screen HTTPResume is
(should open) on. It returns "«DefaultPublicScreen»" if it's open (or
will open) on default public screen.@{par}

@{b}WINX@{ub}, @{b}WINY@{ub}, @{b}WINWIDTH@{ub} and @{b}WINHEIGHT @{ub}
return window x, y coordinate, its width and height respectively. If
window is not open, you will get "-1" for each of of these
values.@{par}

Boolean values return 1 if they are set and 0 if they're not.@{par}

@endnode
@node SET "SET"

@{line}@{b}SET@{ub}@{par}

You can set these values@{par}

@{b}WINX, WINY, WINWIDTH, WINHEIGHT, URL, OUTFILE, PROXY, RANGE,
OVERWRITE, NOCACHE, GMTOFFSET, NODATECHECK, AUTORESUME, ATTEMPTS,
DELAY, STARTDIR, TREE, CONVFROM, CONVTO, MAXNAMELEN, REFERER,
USESYSFONT, NOPROXY, QUICKQUIT, OKSOUND, ERRSOUND, NOWINACTIVATE,
CREATEICONS, AREXXCONSOLE, ONLYIFUPDATED, KEEPDATE, TIMEOUT,
MAXTIMEOUTS, MINCPS, IGNORECPS, NOERRREQ, FORCECOMMENT,
USERAGENT@{ub}@{par}

@{b}WINX@{ub}, @{b}WINY@{ub}, @{b}WINWIDTH@{ub} and @{b}WINHEIGHT@{ub} set
window's x, y coordinate, its width and height respectively, whether
it's open or not (i.e. when it opens, it will use these settings).@{par}

These arguments are the only ones that can be changed while HTTPResume
is downloading the file. If you try to set any other (valid) setting,
RC will be set to 5.@{par}

@{b}SET OUTFILE@{ub} <some file> will change URL if file has URL in
its comment, so if you want to change file @{b}and@{ub} URL, you should
change @{b}OUTFILE@{ub} @{i}first@{ui} and then URL.@{par}

I believe the other values are obvious. You can set boolean values to
TRUE using @{b}SET OVERWRITE@{ub} or @{b}SET OVERWRITE x@{ub} where
x is not 0. To set those to FALSE, use @{b}SET OVERWRITE 0@{ub}.

@endnode
